    icon: `<svg aria-hidden="true" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"/><polyline points="16 7 22 7 22 13"/></svg>`,
    tag: 'ROI',
    title: 'AEO ROI',
    body: 'How to attribute and calculate the return on investment from answer engine and generative engine optimisation programmes.',
    href: '/aeo-roi/',
  },
  {
    icon: `<svg aria-hidden="true" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><path d="M12 2v3m0 14v3M4.22 4.22l2.12 2.12m11.32 11.32 2.12 2.12M2 12h3m14 0h3M4.22 19.78l2.12-2.12M17.66 6.34l2.12-2.12"/></svg>`,
    tag: 'Strategy',
    title: 'Future of GEO',
    body: 'Where generative engine optimisation is heading: platform evolution, measurement maturation, and the long-term strategic outlook.',
    href: '/future-of-geo/',
  },
  {
    icon: `<svg aria-hidden="true" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>`,
    tag: 'Analytics',
    title: 'AI Citations Analytics',
    body: 'Tools, techniques, and data models for tracking where, how often, and how accurately AI platforms cite your brand and content.',
    href: '/ai-citations-analytics/',
  },
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What are the primary KPIs for a GEO programme?',
    a: 'The four primary KPIs for generative engine optimisation are citation frequency (the percentage of relevant queries for which your brand is cited across target AI platforms), AI share of voice (your citation rate relative to competitors for the same query set), brand accuracy score (how correctly AI platforms describe your brand when they do cite it), and cross-platform reach (the number of distinct AI platforms on which your brand is cited consistently). These four metrics form a minimum viable GEO measurement framework.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do you calculate ROI for a GEO programme?',
    a: 'GEO ROI is calculated by attributing a monetary value to AI-driven demand — typically through incrementality testing, assisted conversion tracking, and brand search uplift analysis. The most reliable method is to establish a pre-programme baseline of AI citation frequency and brand search volume, implement optimisation changes, and measure the incremental change in both metrics over 90-day periods. For B2B brands, pipeline influence attribution via CRM tracking provides the most actionable ROI signal.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How often should GEO metrics be reported?',
    a: 'Citation frequency and AI share of voice should be tracked weekly to detect rapid changes caused by platform updates or competitor activity. Monthly reporting is the standard cadence for stakeholder dashboards, combining weekly data into trend lines. Quarterly business reviews should cover ROI, budget efficiency, and strategic adjustments. Annual benchmarking against industry baselines contextualises performance relative to the wider GEO landscape.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is a realistic budget for a GEO programme?',
    a: 'GEO programme budgets vary by organisation size and ambition. Entry-level programmes with manual tracking and basic content optimisation typically require GBP 1,500 to GBP 4,000 per month inclusive of tooling. Mid-tier programmes with dedicated tooling, regular content production, and entity optimisation run GBP 5,000 to GBP 15,000 per month. Enterprise programmes incorporating structured data overhauls, original research production, and full-stack monitoring can exceed GBP 20,000 per month.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do GEO metrics differ from AEO metrics?',
    a: 'GEO metrics and AEO (answer engine optimisation) metrics overlap substantially but are not identical. AEO metrics focus on featured snippet capture rate, voice search answer presence, and People Also Ask visibility — all of which are traditional search signals. GEO metrics focus on citation frequency in generative AI responses, brand entity accuracy, and AI share of voice across LLM platforms. The two frameworks complement each other: AEO metrics improve the content foundations that GEO depends on, while GEO metrics measure whether those foundations are translating into AI citation.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does the future of GEO measurement look like?',
    a: 'GEO measurement is converging towards unified AI visibility dashboards that aggregate citation data across all major generative platforms, attribute AI-driven demand to specific content assets, and benchmark performance against category-level baselines. The emergence of first-party AI analytics — Google Search Console surfacing AI Overview data, and OpenAI introducing publisher analytics — will give brands direct visibility into AI-driven traffic for the first time.',
