---

<Base title={title} description={description} schema={schema} canonical="https://geooptimised.com/geo-metrics/" ogType="website">

  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="container-wide pt-8">
    <ol class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5 font-mono text-xs text-ink-400">
      <li><a href="/" class="transition hover:text-[var(--accent)]">Home</a></li>
      <li aria-hidden="true" class="text-ink-600">/</li>
      <li><a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="transition hover:text-[var(--accent)]">Generative Engine Optimisation</a></li>
      <li aria-hidden="true" class="text-ink-600">/</li>
      <li class="text-ink-200" aria-current="page">GEO Metrics, KPIs &amp; ROI</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <header class="hero-fade relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container-wide grid gap-12 pt-12 pb-20 lg:grid-cols-12 lg:items-center">
      <div class="lg:col-span-7">
        <span class="eyebrow">N9 — Metrics &amp; ROI Hub</span>
        <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
          <span class="grad-text">GEO Metrics, KPIs &amp; ROI</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-300">
          <strong class="text-white">GEO metrics are the measurement layer that turns AI visibility from aspiration into accountable business performance.</strong> This hub covers every quantitative dimension of a generative engine optimisation programme — from citation frequency KPIs and AI share of voice through to budget planning, ROI attribution, and the statistical benchmarks that contextualise your results against the market.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Discuss Your GEO Measurement</a>
          <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="btn btn-ghost">GEO Root Guide</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <div class="card p-6">
          <span class="eyebrow">At a glance</span>
          <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <p class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">4</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-ink-400">Primary KPIs tracked</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">5+</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-ink-400">AI platforms measured</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">7</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-ink-400">Topic guides below</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--accent)]">90-day</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-ink-400">Baseline period</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Seed Card Grid -->
  <section class="container-wide py-20">
    <span class="eyebrow">Topics in this hub</span>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text sm:text-4xl">Metrics, Data &amp; ROI Guides</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
      Each guide below covers a distinct dimension of GEO measurement — from raw statistics and market data through to ROI methodology and long-term strategic forecasting. Use them as a curriculum to build a full-stack GEO measurement capability.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {seeds.map(seed => (
        <a href={seed.href} class="card card-hover block p-7 flex flex-col no-underline group">
          <div class="flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-[var(--line)] text-[var(--accent)]">
            <Fragment set:html={seed.icon} />
          </div>
          <span class="eyebrow mt-5">{seed.tag}</span>
          <h3 class="mt-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50 group-hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">{seed.title}</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300 flex-1">{seed.body}</p>
          <span class="mt-5 inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--accent)]">
            Read guide <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </span>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to Measure Section with table -->
  <section class="container-wide py-20 border-t hair">
    <span class="eyebrow">Measurement Framework</span>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text sm:text-4xl">What to Measure in a GEO Programme</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
      <strong class="text-white">A robust GEO measurement framework covers four reporting layers: platform metrics, brand metrics, content metrics, and commercial metrics.</strong> Each layer answers a different question and informs a different set of decisions. Programmes that track only one layer — typically citation frequency — lack the diagnostic depth to identify root causes and prioritise interventions.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
      The table below maps each metric to its reporting layer, measurement cadence, and the decision it drives. Use it to design a reporting structure that matches your programme's maturity and your stakeholders' requirements.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)]">
      <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
        <thead class="bg-geo-900/60">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-4 font-display font-semibold text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Metric</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-4 font-display font-semibold text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Reporting Layer</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-4 font-display font-semibold text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Cadence</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-4 font-display font-semibold text-ink-100">Decision Driven</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-[var(--line)]">
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Citation Frequency</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Platform</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Weekly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Overall programme health; platform prioritisation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">AI Share of Voice</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Platform</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Monthly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Competitive positioning; budget allocation vs rivals</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Brand Accuracy Score</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Brand</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Monthly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Entity data corrections; content clarification priorities</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Cross-Platform Reach</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Brand</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Monthly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Platform gap identification; retrieval optimisation focus</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Citation Position</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Brand</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Monthly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Content authority investment; competitive differentiation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Cited URL Coverage</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Content</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Monthly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Content audit; underperforming page optimisation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Query Coverage Rate</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Content</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Monthly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Content gap analysis; SEED page production roadmap</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">AI-Attributed Pipeline</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Commercial</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Quarterly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Board-level ROI reporting; budget justification</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Brand Search Uplift</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Commercial</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Quarterly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Demand generation attribution; GEO vs paid comparison</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="hover:bg-geo-900/30 transition-colors">
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-ink-100 whitespace-nowrap">Cost per AI Citation</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Commercial</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Quarterly</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 text-ink-300">Programme efficiency; tooling and agency spend review</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-6 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Platform metrics tell you the scale of your AI visibility; content metrics tell you why you have it.</strong> Brands that measure only citation frequency can confirm whether their programme is working in aggregate but cannot identify which pages are driving citations, which query intents are covered, or where competitors are gaining ground. Content-layer metrics — cited URL coverage and query coverage rate — provide the diagnostic depth that drives optimisation decisions.
      </p>
      <p class="text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
        Commercial metrics are the bridge between GEO activity and business outcomes. Without them, GEO remains a marketing KPI rather than a boardroom conversation. The most important commercial metric is AI-attributed pipeline: deals where the prospect's first touchpoint was an AI-generated answer citing your brand. Capturing this attribution requires first-touch UTM tagging on AI referral traffic, CRM integration, and periodic customer survey data asking prospects how they first encountered your brand.
      </p>
      <p class="text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
        For a full guide to building a measurement system for your programme, see <a href="/how-to-measure-geo/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">how to measure GEO</a>. For the statistical context that frames your results, visit our <a href="/geo-statistics/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO statistics</a> guide. The broader discipline is covered in our <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">generative engine optimisation</a> root guide.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
  <section class="container-wide py-20 border-t hair">
    <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text sm:text-4xl">GEO Metrics: Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl divide-y divide-[var(--line)]">
      {faqs.map(faq => (
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-base font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            <span>{faq.q}</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
            <p class="pb-5 text-sm text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">{faq.a}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Banner -->
  <section class="container-wide py-20">
    <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl dot-grid">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-[rgba(var(--accent-glow),.12)] via-transparent to-transparent"></div>
      <div class="relative px-8 py-16 text-center sm:px-16">
        <span class="eyebrow">GEO Measurement</span>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-ink-50 sm:text-4xl">Ready to Put Numbers on Your AI Visibility?</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 mx-auto max-w-2xl text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
          GEOoptimised builds measurement frameworks that connect AI citation data to commercial outcomes. Whether you need a baseline assessment, an ongoing reporting infrastructure, or help making the ROI case internally, we can help. Get in touch to discuss your programme.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Discuss GEO Measurement</a>
          <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="btn btn-ghost">Back to GEO Root Guide</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item button').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const item = btn.closest('.faq-item');
        const answer = item.querySelector('.faq-answer');
        const icon = item.querySelector('.faq-icon');
        const isOpen = btn.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
        document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item button[aria-expanded="true"]').forEach(other => {
          if (other !== btn) {
            other.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
            other.closest('.faq-item').querySelector('.faq-answer').style.maxHeight = '0';
            other.closest('.faq-item').querySelector('.faq-icon').style.transform = '';
          }
        });
        btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', isOpen ? 'false' : 'true');
        answer.style.maxHeight = isOpen ? '0' : answer.scrollHeight + 'px';
        icon.style.transform = isOpen ? '' : 'rotate(45deg)';
      });
    });
  </script>

</Base>
